reviews.review_text: It was exactly what we were looking for in breakfast- RICE!! yes, we had this huge bowl for breakfast and we love it! Servings are pretty good and you get food value at affordable prices. Had their Ebiten and Mega Bowl and youll really get what you see on their menu. Downside would be, we ate inside the store and we were just about to start our day, we definitely smell like their food the whole day
Weve tried 3 dishes here. All of it are really good.  Personally, spicy chicken udon is the best. I love the spicy noodles and chicken karaage! Staff are friendly and ready to serve you! Food

Ebi Ten is the best place to go when I dont  pack a lunch for work. It is across the street from the Central Library and I can take my selection up to the rooftop garden and have my lunch there. The prices are reasonable and the food seems to be healthy. I can get in and out quickly as long as no one is hanging around the grab-and-go section.
Unexpectedly really good food, and it wasn t expensive! Food serving at a good portion.
The large beef udon went up in price, its $11.40 but still affordable and delicious!
Delicious food, friendly staff and clean place. The only downside is that there are not many seats. On a good day, it s nice to have food to go and eat outside library

Update: Tried the Katsu Curry Deluxe which was delicious! Beef Yakisoba was just okay Perfect for lunch! Really hits the spot Got me an Ebi-Ten Bowl with a miso soup add-on, great combo of delicious flavors and even picked up a Pork Katsu Bun which tasted unreal for under $3 They have a quick Cold Fridge grab n go and a Hot Lantern grab n go at the entrance! Definitely worth a check out!

Food is tasty, comes quickly, reasonably priced, and staff are in credibly polite. For a quick downtown lunch, Ebi-Ten is one of my go-to. They also have a convenience store style shelf of grab-and-go food for the convenience. Great for office workers and students.

Very happy I tried out this place when I was initially hesitant. Food here was just superb and portions were generous, plus it s in downtown so it s really easy to get there. They also have a patio area which is nice as the inside of the store isn t very spacious. They don t accept cash though, so make sure you have a debit/credit card if you go here!

This place is amazinggggg. So many options for a meal or if you just want to grab a small snack to go! Larger dishes are a bit pricey for their portion size but boy are they delicious! Their grab and go section runs out of stock fast so come early during lunch rush to ensure you get a good selection. Always my go to for spam musubi. Yum!

Casual inexpensive (per YVR standards!) across the street from my hotel. Bright and clean.  Most of customers ordering takeout. Staff friendly and very efficient. Small place, tables/chairs for approx 10 dine in customers, mix of US/Asian music playing in background. Waited approx 5 mins for my order to be prepared. Katsu was plentiful, moist and crispy.  Udon noodles were chewy and broth beefy flavorful. Damn, who would have thought, great value for your money

Amazing value, delicious food, and expedient service. It s the perfect trifecta of Japanese fast food! Ebiten bowl is a must try. The curry is pretty good for the price as well. The smaller to-go hot food on the shelves are a decent addition to your meal. This place has tons of regulars from people working in the area. Highly recommended especially if you re grabbing something quick and cheap.
Unique, delicious, super friendly staff serving wonderful culinary creations! Tummy love!

Amazing food! Always fresh, great portion sizes and well priced. The Mega Bowl is the best, they nail the tempura every time - delicious!! My favorite place to eat on my lunch break. Good location, friendly staff. Thanks guys!

Walked past and couldn t resist the price so we thought we d give it a try and I want to say it was my favourite udon of our trip to Vancouver. I got both the beef and tempura for my udon and the flavour of the broth with the beef was so good! I wish I had found that place sooner. The tempura wasn t half bad for the price and everything we ordered came to about $20 and we were quite full afterwards. If I m ever in the downtown area and need a quick and delicious bite, I know where to go!
Fresh and tasty. Great value & price. Doesnt ask to tip when you takeout.... very refreshing. Go here for lunch!

Delicious food, clean place, cheap food, nice staff and cozy setting , I ordered Tako Bomb and Udon , so delicious and yummy, I do recommend this place , one if the best street Japanese food I ever eat .
I came here once during the afternoon. Food is reasonably priced, looks good, and tastes great. Staff is polite.

I have been going to Ebi Ten for years now. Anyone who knows me knows how much I love Japanese food. Fast food Japanese food is so good! I always get the chicken teriyaki don with a poached egg and extra salad on the side. The chicken pieces are nice and sweet with just the right amount of fat and skin. Pre covid I would add pickled ginger on top. Ive had the katsu curry here a few times as well, also with a poached egg and pickled ginger. The curry has a nice spicy kick to it and the pork pieces are breaded and fried perfectly. It would make me so happy if they opened another location! Preferably closer to Burnaby!
Their grab and go section has a good selection of cheap and tasty lunch items. Great location next to the library as well.

Ebi-Ten is a staple for people who want fairly priced and delicious cafe-style japanese food. Its a popular place among people who work in the area so dont be surprised if theres a line up. Ebi-Ten also has grab-and-go items like onigiris. If youre lucky you can get yourself a spam musubi.

Been coming to this place for years. They have very nice quality Japanese meals, the prices are also fair. Portions are big and the food is fresh and leaves you feeling guilt free. The mega bowl is my favourite but everything on the menu is solid. The onigiri are also a good choice at lunch time!
Very delicious and good service.

This stuff was BUSSIN BUSSIN Much like the katsu/curry fast food shops in Japan. Great flavour served in minutes. They have a variety of katsu and tempura don (with & without curry), and udon (including curry udon, my fav Japanese homey food). This place is authentic and is great for a quick, filling, delicious bite. Its currently offering some limited dine-in seating, and takeout is easy and well-packaged. Great prices for the size. As the name of the restaurant suggests, be sure to try their prawn tempura (trust me, its worth it!)
The California roll is actually good. The avocado salad is also good. Love that they offer affordable items downtown. Clean and tasty.

Found this Japanese cafe style joint accidentally as it is only two blocks from my hotel.    Had Katsu curry for take out.    It was good portion and fairly priced.    Remind me of many of those affordable and delicious Japanese cafe I ate in when I travelled to in Japan a few times in the past!    Highly recommend this joint to anyone who wants to try honest, authentic and delicious Japanese home made style food!   Employees are polite and courteous!

I had the Katsu Curry with rice and also ate some of the takoyaki my mother ordered. The Katsu wasn t as melt in your mouth as I would have liked but it still tasted pretty good. Few things can give me more dopamine than finishing off those last forkfuls of rice coated in curry sauce. Takoyaki is better than the ones I ate when studying at Davao City and prepared much quicker to boot. Service was done with a smile as well. I had quite a good experience here.

The place is right outside the Vancouver Public library. I casually went in for a quick bite. Ordered sea weed salad and Sushi. The taste was amazing especially the salad. Also very pocket friendly. The service was quick and I would rate this place highly for a quick bite if you are visiting the library. Better than other outlets in its vicinity.

Japanese fast food restaurant  is right! My food arrived so quickly!!! I was hungry and did not have a lot of time to wait for food. The food was very fresh and very crunchy! People who works there, they were so friendly and this place is budget friendly place! I will come again with my friends. Small place so I would not recommend big groups only 2~4 people.

Best #2 deep fried pork cutlet curry rice: exceptionally juicy pork!  Curry is not spicy at all but nice to eat with the rice, though I personally prefer more spicy. A good alternative amongst Japanese restaurant on Robson Street!

I don t eat Japanese curry often so I can t compare much  it s my first time eating curry cutlet though, and I enjoyed every bite!  Crispy cooked pork, rice was amazing, the pickled vegggies on the side was PERFECT pairing, and the portion was huge! Con: I wish I asked for curry sauce on the side because it was quite drenched. Do yourself a favour and just ask for sauce on side so you can add to your liking.
Reasonable price and amazing tasting food. The fried shrimp goes so well with curry! You will be thinking about how good it was for long afterwards.
I always enjoy the reasonably authentic and well priced curry here. Bonus star: fast check out and not prompting for tips - excellent.

Very delicious katsu pork curry for its price. The piece of katsu is outstanding , very good quality pork which tastes amazing and juicy even without the curry sauce. Portion is very good too ! Highly recommended .

EBI TEN in Vancouver is a fantastic restaurant for Japanese cuisine. The Katsu Curry on Rice is a standout dish, with the perfectly fried katsu and rich, flavorful curry. The Yakiniku Beef is also a must-try, with tender slices of beef that are cooked to perfection. If youre in the mood for something simple and satisfying, the Plain Udon is a great choice. The noodles are cooked just right and the broth is deliciously savory. The portion sizes are generous, and the prices are reasonable for the quality of food you receive. Overall, EBI TEN is a great spot for a casual meal with friends or a quick lunch on-the-go. The service is friendly and attentive, and the atmosphere is cozy and welcoming. I highly recommend this restaurant for anyone who loves Japanese cuisine.

Ebi-Ten is a Japanese fast-food restaurant that serves rice and noodle bowls, as well as small appetizers and sushi for grab and go if youre in a hurry. Weve been loyal customers for 10+ years! Their beef yaki-udon and katsu curry are my favorites. Service is friendly and fast, each order takes less than 10mins. Quality of food is excellent. Best of all, a meal with a drink will only cost you around $14 including tax and tips. It beats any other fast-food restaurant in downtown Vancouver. Note: they are closed on Sundays.
Try their mega bowl with noodles. You will fall in love with this place.
I love this place. Very authentic to what I experienced in Japan in the past. Their onigiri are fresh and delicious too and a great selection of drinks.

The best grab-and-go sushi Ive found since Ive been working downtown. Before COVID their selection used to be a little bigger, but there are still good options for onigiri and other rolls. I love their takoyaki, which are very popular during lunch rush. Occasionally Ill order something off the menu too, like the curry udon. Everythings delicious and, just as importantly, cheap! I can comfortably eat lunch for $10 or less.

There is nothing but great things to say about Ebi-Ten. Ive been going here for the past 4 years, and theyve never failed to impress. Either youre dining in with a hot plate of curry or taking out some rolls with a couple onigiri, the custom service, and staff are excellent. All items on the menu are priced appropriately. Sit in dishes worth getting are the Deluxe Curry, Ebi Fry Curry, and Kimchi Yaki Udon. All to-go items are worth it: assorted sushi rolls, katsu sando, musubi, menchi katsu, chicken karaage, takoyaki, and all the Onigiris. All are perfectly for a sit-in meal, a quick lunch, or a picnic at a park.
Best takoyaki Ive ever had, EVER. I think its  deep fried after pan frying. The deluxe curry was yummy with the sauce. Good prices as well. A nice little place to stop for a meal
Very tasty reasonably priced Japanese curry and rice dishes. The katsu curry is my go-to.
My favourite place to go to! Best food at reasonable rate!

Great food very good price had the mega bowl the tofu is delicious. The katsu curry is also one of the best price to food ratio. Their staff is very friendly and the space to eat is spacious many tables very clean. Really recommended the chicken teriyaki bowl!

This is my favorite Japanese curry restaurant in Vancouver. Delicious at a reasonable price. Although it is a takeout restaurant, they do not ask for a tip like in Japan. Also the service is good. Contrary to pressing the tip with %, even though the other places are takeout.
Very delicious, freshly fried, and consistent flavours. The tartar sauce (?) is so good!!
This place is absolutely fantastic I eat here many times a week. Highly recommend.

Enjoy going here to pick up a quick lunch. My go to are the two hand rolls for $5 plus a spam musubi. Have also tried the ebi ten bowl which was very filling with generous portions. Would like to try the udon next time.

Good variety and taste FOR THE PRICE. if youre looking for fine dining or healthy options this isnt the place. Its fast food and is prepared somewhat similar to other fast food joints where they have a lot of food already cooked and they just throw it together. Thats also why its super speedy. Good place to go if youre on a break during work or if you just dont feel like paying too much for sustenance. I recommend the curry. Sushi isnt bad either!

Really love this place. In 2019 I ate there for 5 tines or more. Three years after, I was just visiting Vancouver again and had to come back to Ebi-Ten. The food hasnt changed, its still so tasty and with a cheap price. I recommend this restaurant at 100%
Fastest service Ive encountered to date. I think it was less the 5 minutes from placing my order to me getting out the door and back to my office
I had the Japanese curry with shrimp and was really surprised because I didnt know that and it was really good so Ill definitely go there again, also the onigiri were great.
This is the best food in Vancouver! Only order delivery, never been in the restaurant. I love the Fried Fish Curry. What a treat. I am a loyal customer.

9.98 (tax included) for this meal. Very filling. Microwave available to heat up cold fridge foods. Would recommend getting their cheap fridge foods as you can get really good value from it ($6.25!!). Super affordable!
Just has the curry udon and it was delicious!!  They are fast, clean and friendly.  Premade fresh sushi rolls too.  It takes me back to living in Japan in such a lovely way!

I enjoy the to-go sushi rolls here so much I eat them without soy sauce. The rice is perfectly cooked and unseasoned the way I like it, the avocados used are perfectly ripe and the seafood ingredients are fresh and flavourful. I like to get salmon avocado roll and california roll. I also enjoy spam musubi, takoyaki, and onigiri if I feel like eating extra carbs that day. Basically have not tried anything I didnt like, and service is friendly :-)
Tried the Katsu curry yesterday and it was awesome! katsu was perfectly crispy on the outside and juicy inside, not greasy either. and the thick curry was so tasty.. will definitely be back :)
Solid spam musubi and onigiri! Great place to drop by for a quick snack.
Plentiful, tasty, and inexpensive. Perfect combo for everyday cuisine. Had the deluxe curry!
A must eat at! If you want amazing food! This place is only second to chilli dogs!
The staff are super polite. The food tastes good, well proportioned, and inexpensive. My wife and I are regulars. We share the Mabo Tofu and are very satisfied.
Reasonable price and delicious food. Their ready-to-eat lunchbox is super cheap. Also fast order and serve. Always long lineup during lunch time.

Stopped by at lunch because McDonalds happened to be closed for the day.  Tried the Mega Bowl and loved it.  Tempura was so fresh, and the mapo tofu was so tasty.  Came again the next lunch and tried the chicken karage and takoyaki.  Those were very good as well. A lot of people, but very quick kitchen!  Grab a take out order and sit on the library steps!
My favourite place for cheap and fast food. I sometimes bus 30 minutes just to eat here. Everything tastes so good but the mabo tofu set is especially good.
They always have a great selection of Japanese food with very reasonable price and generous portion. This is a perfect spot to have lunch or early dinner when you study from the public library

I was in there and my paper bag ripped open and scattered all my belongings all over the floor. The girl at the front counter was very nice and helped me pick up all my stuff. Great food and great people

Im going to Ebi-Ten probably once a week for the last 5 years. I just love the food and the staff there. It might looks like a fast food because its cheap and quick BUT it is as good if not better than most of the traditional japanese restaurant in Vancouver.
Tried the Katsu Curry, deep fried pork cutlet with Japanese curry on rice. Fast and delicious, unexpectedly good! My friend tried the Ebiten bowl, really good too.

This place reminds me of those family restaurants in Japan that serve simple yet delicious dishes like curry rice, tendon, and gyudon. They also sell premade bento boxes, sushi rolls, and some tempura boxes on the side.
Fantastic prices and fantastic food, you can get a filling lunch here at a better price than anywhere else downtown in my opinion.
Ebi ten is fast food.  Make no mistake. But so much better than American fast food. Their most expensive meal is only 15 bucks. But you can get full and happy for 10.
My go to place for quick lunches and meals. Good price for all items, especially the bentos and cold bowls.

First-time ordering at this restaurant through Skip the Dishes. Everything is absolutely delicious. I will order from there more often now that I know about it. Thank you Ebi-Ten and Skip the dishes for your advertisement.

FAST! Grab a fresh, affordable, fresh made lunch or dinner. The sushi/salad/seaweed/karage 2 for $6.00 is an awesome deal (it does sell out by 2pm or earlier daily). Mabu tofu and Mayo buta-don are favorites of mine. Bottles of Ito-en tea, roll cake and flan pudding are a treat as well.
Great food and fast service. Good sized portion also for 8 bucks. Have a new favorite place. I want to try all their food.
mega-bowl+miso-soup is great
Staff is super sweet, always.  Love their sushi to go rolls - specifically the yam roll which is delicious and a great bang for your buck!
Such delicious food and the only place that didn t raise prices after inflation. Thank you Ebi-Ten. I will keep coming.
Came by today and grabbed the Mega Bowl. Highly recommend! Reminds me of a better version of Matsuya / Sukiya. Keep up the great work :)
If you must eat fast food, let it be at Ebi Ten! Donburi and noodle meals are all delicious... and you cant refuse a plate of Takoyaki to share (or not) with your friend!!
Great for a cheap fast and delicious meal before a soccer game. Their chicken karage is particularly good.
Its 5 stars for what it is.  Theyve been there for years for a reason! Reliable, neighborly and pretty good value.

During the week, stop in and get a spam and egg onigiri , totally worth it. $4 for two and you will be full. Unless you understand this, you have no idea of what you are missing. You betcha! Japan style breakfast.
Those udon noodles are delicious!!! Loved every bit of it. Great spot and quick service, very friendly staff.
Great place for quick and delicious Japanese style curry katsu
Im addicted to their musubi. The most delicious snack ever!
Food is delicious!! Amazing people food always on point. Must go if you need a bite! 10/10
One of the best Japanese fast food I have ever eat, this place its so good , I have tried another Japaneses places but this one still in Top 1, good food, good prices and good service.
Customer service and food great
Perfect japanese fast food place. Good food and good price. For me,their curry rice is the best
Good, fast, and cheap. what more can you ask for? Simple, quick, and easy lunch. Used to have it almost every day when I was working around the area.
The mcdonalds version of japanese food! fast delicious and cheap! what more can i say? always great for a quick, wallet-friendly bite!
Good food at reasonable prices. Place is clean too and service is rapid
Tasty and delicious Japanese favourites in the heart of downtown Vancouver.
Fantastic! Authentic! Large generous portions and the taste is just simply incredible :)
Mega bowl tastes good, good mapo dofu, good tempura, good takoyaki. Service is fast.
Many options, good prices, good Japanese fast food. Great for quick, inexpensive eats.
This is one of my favorite lunch places. Cheap, delicious and super efficient!
My fav place downtown for a quick lunch or supper. Buta mayo don.  Yum!
Great location, good prices, amazing for picking up a quick meal if youre in the area.
